Peru Stocks: Brocal, Edegel, Ferreyros, IRL, Maple, Minsur

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-07-19T19:10:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-19/peru-stocks-brocal-edegel-ferreyros-irl-maple-minsur.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 2:42 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index rose 2.9 percent to 21,905.70. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index gained 2.3 percent to 2,757.71.  Industrial and banking stocks gained as investors bet
President-elect Ollanta Humala will name an investor-friendly
finance minister after retaining central bank president Julio Velarde for another five-year term, said Gustavo Urrutia, the
chief economist at brokerage Inteligo SAB in Lima.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1)  (FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for
Caterpillar Inc., jumped 6.3 percent to 2.71 soles.  Maple Energy
Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas producer with operations
in Peru, rose 5.4 percent to $1.18 after crude advanced in New
York.  Grana y Montero SA (GRAMONC1)  (GRAMONC1 PE), Peru’s largest
construction firm, gained 6.9 percent to 6.2 soles.  Banco
Continental SA (CONTINC1)  (CONTINC1 PE), the local unit of  Spain ’s Banco
Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA, climbed 4.6 percent to 6.59 soles.
Edegel SA (EDEGELC1 PE), the Peru unit of Spain’s Endesa SA,
rose 4.4 percent to 1.67 soles.  Miners gained as metals advanced in New York and  London .  Rio Cristal Resources Corp. (RCZ)  , a Canadian zinc
exploration company, rose 5.3 percent to 20 cents.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1) 
(MINSURI1 PE), Peru’s largest tin producer, advanced 4.8 percent
to 3.90 soles. Sociedad Minera El Brocal SAA (BROCALC1 PE), a
silver producer, gained 4.2 percent to 42 soles. Sociedad Minera
Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of Freeport-McMoRan Copper
& Gold Inc., climbed 3.5 percent to $41.90.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL) 
, a U.K. minerals explorer with a gold mine in Peru,
rose 3.2 percent to $1.29.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  